contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|NYC}} '''[[New York City]]''' is the most populous city in the United States. '''NYC''' may also refer to: {{TOC right}} == New York related == * [[.nyc]], a proposed top level internet domain for New York City * [[New York City (video game)|''New York City'' (video game)]], a 1984 Atari 400/800/XL and Commodore 64 video game * [[New York Central Railroad]], a Northeastern railroad from 1831–1968 * [[NYC Condom]], a condom brand * The IATA code for all New York City-area airports, including: ** [[John F. Kennedy International Airport]] (JFK) ** [[LaGuardia Airport]] (LGA) ** [[Newark Liberty International Airport]] (EWR) == Music == * [[NYC (band)]], a 2010 Japanese boy band * [[NYC (Interpol song)|"NYC" (Interpol song)]] * [[NYC (Prince song)|"NYC" (Prince song)]] * "[[NYC (There's No Need to Stop)]]", a song by The Charlatans * "NYC", a song by Kevin Rudolf from ''[[In the City (Kevin Rudolf album)|In the City]]'' * "N.Y.C.", a song by Steve Earle from ''[[El Corazón]]'' * "N.Y.C.", a song from the musical ''[[Annie (musical)|Annie]]'' == Other == * [[National Youth Competition (rugby league)]] * [[North York Centre]], a district in Toronto * ''Northern Yacht Club'' (established 1824), which became the ''Royal Northern Yacht Club'' in 1830, now the [[Royal Northern and Clyde Yacht Club]] ==See also== * [[New York City (disambiguation)]] * [[New York, New York (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation}}
